sources.description:
Two spoiled rich people marooned on a rogue luxury liner, transform from clueless socialites into slapstick survivalistsâ€”battling swordfish, outwitting cannibals, and improvising submarine escapes while their floating fortress careens from nautical absurdity to underwater mayhem.

Original Title: The Navigator

Directed by Buster Keaton, Donald Crisp

Main Cast:
Buster Keaton - Rollo Treadway
Kathryn McGuire - Betsy O'Brien
Frederick Vroom - John O'Brien (Betsy's father)

Uncredited cast:
Noble Johnson - Cannibal Chief 
Clarence Burton - Spy
H.N. Clugston - Spy

Genres: Colorized, Comedy, Slapstick, Adventure, Romance
Release Date: October 13, 1924 
Filming Location: Aboard the SS Buford
